text: Garrett's Island House is a historic home located near Plymouth, Washington County, North Carolina. It was built about 1760, and is a 1 1/2-story, Georgian / Federal style frame dwelling with a gambrel roof. It has a shed roofed front porch and double-shouldered exterior brick chimney. Garrett's Island House is thought to be the oldest extant dwelling in Washington County. It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 2001. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in North Carolina Category:Georgian architecture in North Carolina Category:Federal architecture in North Carolina Category:Houses completed in 1760 Category:Houses in Washington County, North Carolina Category:National Register of Historic Places in Washington County, North Carolina
